Aug 27 2009 	Clean great location not bad for London	I have heard that it's very hard to find a decent priced, clean hotel in London. A friend of a friend recommended this one and it certainly was fine for two nights!We opted for the shared bath, which meant we were only paying 93 Pounds a night (which for London is a bargain). The room was very pleasant with a sink and a wardrobe and very, very clean. There was also a nice tea service put out for us. The shared bathroom was nothing spectacular, just a tiled shower and toilet, but the water was hot and like the rest of the hotel, the bathroom was immaculate. We only stayed two nights, but never had trouble accessing the bathroom, even though there were other people on our floor.I am in good shape, but must admit dragging my suitcase up three very steep flights of stairs wasn't as easy as I'd hoped. Still, it's only that one trip up that's difficult and a good workout otherwise. Stll, travellers who would not be able to handle the stairs have no other options and should not stay at this hotel.The breakfast was a traditional English breakfast and I had not had time to call ahead and ask about vegetarian options. The staff tried to accomodate, and really, it didn't matter that much to me. I imagine if I'd given them more warning, they might have been able to accomodate my request.The staff is very helpful. There are maps and guides in the television room and we borrowed the London guide for the day. Our host booked a taxi for us in the morning as well. There is wireless in this hotel, but we found it only worked in the television room, which meant traipsing up and down those stairs!The hotel is on a quiet side street. We heard a bit of traffic from the busier street one over, but overall it was very quiet for being in Central London!I've heard nightmare reviews of London budget hotels and will say that as long as you can handle the stairs and don't mind sharing a bathroom, this hotel is clean, great location and great staff.	
