Aug 7 2007	You'd never find by chance.	Kensington; an historic, classy (the women!), part of London. I'd got the bus there, and wondered to the north of Kensington High St, expecting to find many hotels; but there were none. I asked a cabbie, who told me about the Vicarage - even so it was so discretely signed, that if you stood at the street end and looked, you wouldn't n see it.Property prices here mean that hotels and pubs, and other businesses, are being squeezed out,. The 'Vicarage Private Hotel' (to give it its full name) suvrives. But, for how much longer ? The only other hotel in the street closed this year. The Vicarage is the only small hotel remaining in this part of London. It is near two GREAT pubs; 'The Churchill' on Kensington Church St, and the Elephant and Castle (nearby). On a summer's night, sleep with your window open,the sounds of London drifting into your ears. Help keep this unique hotel open !	
