Mar 22 2004	Great location and affordable	I got this recommendation from Rick Steeve's book and was pleasantly surprised with the location, convenience to the tube and accomodations. The hotel is located between the Notting Hill and Kensington High Street tube stations. It's in a nice quiet culdesac with minimal traffic noise, and walking distance to Portobello Road. The complimentary breakfast was more than adequate and the rooms and shared bathroom/shower was very clean and maintained. It was also nice that they provided a tea kettle, tea, and hot cocoa in the room. As with most small hotels, there was no &quot;lift&quot; so if you are on the top floor, get ready to hoist your luggage about 5 flights of stairs.	
