Jan 30 2004	Excellent value - excellent location!	My husband and two young daughters stayed here at the end of September 2003. This place has a lot going for it. Incredible location (Nottingham tube is one block one way, Kensington is just a couple of blocks another way), it's extremely quiet, and you get amazing value for London. The stairs ARE killers, and we were on the 4th floor in a quad. (They call it the 3rd floor over there). That's okay, my husband and I are in good shape, but we made absolutely sure we had everything we needed before we'd leave our room for a day of sightseeing. Huge groan if we'd get to the lobby and realize our camera was still in our room. Speaking of the lobby, that is a little bothersome that they allow smoking in the tv room right off the lobby. I don't smoke, but I'm not a huge anti-smoking snob either. The tv room was 12 x 12 and circulation came from a window cracked 1/2 an inch. Bathrooms were down the hall, but not once did we have to wait. I've seen comments about the staff, and all I can say about that is - &quot;What staff?&quot; We checked in and met a person in the office, but other than that time it was difficult to come across anybody who appeared to work there. (Excluding breakfast time). We weren't asking for anyone, so maybe somebody would have crawled out of a corner if we had called out in the lobby, I don't know. The rooms were quite clean, as were the bathrooms. I thought the size of the room was ample. We were traveling with another couple staying in a hotel in London who had to check out immediately because their room was so small they both couldn't have their suitcases open at the same time. Space is limited in London hotels, so I felt like our room was palatial in comparison. The only warning I'll have to sound is: They are in the middle of a big remodel and it sounds like a lot of their rooms are having bathrooms put in. I have a hunch that this bargain hotel might not be quite the bargain when the remodel is over. Bottom line: If you don't need a lot of fawning over you by hotel staff and you want a great location, a clean, safe, quiet, comfortable place, I don't think you can beat this one in London. (For the price).	
