Aug 16 2003	Good B	Our family of four (wife and I, two teenage boys) stayed here in a quad room for three nights in June 2002. The location is good, near the tube, with lots of shopping and restaurants nearby, and on a quiet street. Our room was small, with a double and two twin beds, and a boudoir, dresser, table, two chairs, and a wash basin. The carpet was old, worn and stained. It was good for sleeping, but not a place you'd go back to relax in. The bathrooms (down the hall) were clean and we had no problem accessing them. The breakfast was wonderful. But if you want an elevator, forget it, and you'll be sharing TV and phone, so if you need these a lot, this may not be the place for you. I found the staff business-like, but not overly friendly. I'd probably stay here again if I only needed a double room, but the quad room seemed a little crammed.	
Feb 11 2003	The Vicarage Hotel is an outstanding value	I have stayed at the Vicarage Hotel five or six times and each time was excellent. The full English breakfasts are outstanding and the rooms are stocked with antiques. You must share the TV room on the first floor and showers and bath rooms. There are no TVs nor phones in the individual rooms. There is no elevator to assist in luggage transport. The staff are very friendly, responsive. They take no credit cards nor US dollars, except for the reservation prepayment. It is a very lovely place and I will stay there again and again. It is close to the Kensington High tube entrance. There are a number of excellent restaurants and a super Internet Cafe within walking distance.	
